    "information_content_info_8Egqwz": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "richtext_BT7hai": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>The increase in Gold Price Today in India has been attributed to the growing need for Gold and the increased sensitivity of the Indian Gold Market to global indicators. A rise in Gold Prices indicates an increase in Geopolitical Instability, heightened Inflation Expectations, and increased volatility of currencies, including the U.S. dollar. As India imports over 90% of its gold needs, the Rupee's depreciation enhances the perceived value of gold in India.</p><p>Much of the Gold Market's upward trend can be attributed to the increased purchasing activity during the \"Wedding Season,\" which takes place before and during Festival Season times. In addition to this increase in demand from consumers, during periods of International Economic uncertainty, Investors tend to become more interested in investing their wealth into Gold and move their capital from Riskier Investments to \"Safe Haven Investments\" such as Gold.</p><p>As such, the current rise in the Gold Price is a strong indicator that the Consumer should consider buying Gold by either locking in prices or closely tracking the market for future potential declines in price. Long-term Investors should view the recent increase in the price of Gold as a long-term forecast for Gold's value as a \"Safe Haven\" Investment, especially when compared to an unpredictable Stock Market.</p><p>As Global Economic conditions continue to evolve in conjunction with Domestic Indian Economic conditions, today’s increase in Gold Price reflects the value of Gold to both the Indian Consumer and Investor. Each day, updated information will allow you to remain informed about your decisions regarding Gold.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
