    "information_content_info_RrD7HT": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_fJ8wbH": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Gold Purity 101: Meaning of 24K, 22K, 18K, And 14K",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Gold Purity 101: Meaning of 24K, 22K, 18K, And 14K",
            "heading_level": "h2",
            "heading_id": "purity",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_JUjair": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>The purity of Gold is measured in Karats, and gold comes in a variety of purities. Fluctuations in purity contribute to a lot of different aspects, for example, the durability of the jewelry, the price of gold per gram, and more. Let’s look at different karat purities and understand exactly how pure each karat purity is.</p>"
          }
        },
        "heading_j3Ay7Q": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "24 Karat Gold",
          "settings": {
            "text": "24 Karat Gold",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "twentyfourkarat",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_BhKCqn": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>24 karat gold also known as gold 24k is 99.9% pure, and is the purest form of gold available for purchase.  Fun fact, pure gold is bright yellow and is actually really, really soft and is not a practical choice for wearable jewelry. Thus, it has become the primary choice for investment purchases namely gold coins and bars. On this page, you can find the updated value of 24k gold price in India. It is important to know the updated value on a daily basis to make an informed decision at the time of purchase.</p>"
          }
        },
        "heading_Rdq4aW": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "22 Karat Gold",
          "settings": {
            "text": "22 Karat Gold",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "twentytwokarat",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_jATpUz": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>22 karat gold, also known as 916 gold, is 91.6% pure. It is more durable than 24k gold which makes it an ideal choice for traditional Indian bridal jewelry and everyday pieces. What makes this gold really popular is the fact that it retains a high resale value while being durable enough to be used for intricate designs and to hold important gemstones. If you’re looking for 916 gold rate today, or the updated 22 carat hallmark gold price today, you can refer to the rates displayed on the page to make an informed decision when purchasing high quality gold.</p>"
          }
        },
        "heading_c8HkPt": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "18 Karat Gold",
          "settings": {
            "text": "18 Karat Gold",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "eighteenkarat",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_bmtxde": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Coming in at 75% purity, 18 karat gold is a popular choice for making diamond or gemstone studded jewelry. Because this purity of gold contains a greater amount of other chemicals, it is sturdier than 22k gold and is the ideal choice for holding valuable gemstones or diamonds. You should check the 18kt gold rate today that is displayed on our web page before making a purchase to make an informed decision.</p>"
          }
        },
        "heading_MPBUgd": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Modern Choices",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Modern Choices",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "modern",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_e3CmRG": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>As fashion trends continue to evolve, gold plated jewelry and other hues of gold have started gaining popularity. Alternative gold options like white and rose gold are also becoming a very common choice in the modern gold marketing and shopping scenarios due to the contemporary and classic appeal of their hues.  White gold price and rose gold price are very similar to yellow gold prices at the same purity. </p>"
          }
        }
      },
