    "information_content_info_NC6H6E": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_YeYxbQ": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Historic Price Trends: How Past Prices Predict Gold’s Future",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Historic Price Trends: How Past Prices Predict Gold’s Future",
            "heading_level": "h2",
            "heading_id": "historic",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_ee3pVH": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>In India, gold has traditionally been seen as a symbol of status, prosperity, and stability. Over time, it has not only retained its value but appreciated consistently, only interrupted by global and historic events. So without further ado, let’s deep dive and see what the trend of historical price of gold tells us about its future. </p>"
          }
        },
        "heading_abkKqD": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Gold Chart & Price Movement",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Gold Chart & Price Movement",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "chart",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_MzJLMV": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Whenever tracking gold price movement, referring to a gold price chart, or gold chart, is a must. As you track fluctuations over the last decade, you’ll notice a strong yet steady rise in the gold price trend. It has had a bullish performance over the last decade, barring a few months of uncertainty or turmoil. While smaller fluctuations can be seen in the gold price last 10 days, it is mainly due to passing news, currency rates, and local demand but as you gauge the gold rate last 10 years, you will notice consistent bullish growth we were talking about earlier which makes gold a great investment even in modern times.</p>"
          }
        },
        "heading_WDPmbe": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Calculating Returns From Gold Investments",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Calculating Returns From Gold Investments",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "returns",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_yTMT6U": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>If you’re planning a long term investment, you should check the return in gold in the last 10 years and then compare it with other forms of investment. You’ll be shocked to know, gold has frequently delivered returns higher than quite a lot of FDs, RDs, and in some cases, even equity mutual funds. Alternatively, you can also calculate your ROI by comparing the 10 year old gold rate today with the current gold rate and get an accurate idea of your returns. Historic insights and reliability are the very backbones of investment, helping investors make confident decisions about when to enter the market, how long to hold, and what’s the ideal time to leave. </p>"
          }
        }
      },
