    "information_content_info_hj4WiD": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_P7pLVp": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Factors Affecting Gold Price In IndiaBlock",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Factors Affecting Gold Price In India",
            "heading_level": "h2",
            "heading_id": "factors",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_fUxym3": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>As discussed earlier, there are a variety of factors, both international and domestic, that influence the local gold rates. Here are some major factors affecting gold price in modern times, in India:</p><ul><li>International Gold Prices: The gold price international market is the primary factor that influences our national rates. Usually quoted in USD per ounce, these prices are then used to derive the INR per gram value after accounting for the prevailing currency exchange rates. </li><li>Currency Exchange Rates: India imports most of its gold, hence gold price in dollar influences our local rates. As mentioned earlier, international markets calculate gold rate in dollar per ounce, which is then converted into INR per gram. Naturally, the value of Indian Rupee is weighed against the dollar and that also becomes a factor in influencing our national gold rate. </li><li>Inflation & Interest Rates: It is a well known fact that gold serves as a hedge against inflation. As inflation rises and interest rates fall, the value of gold appreciates due to its increased demand. </li><li>Geopolitical Tensions: Wars, pandemics, and financial crisis can negatively impact the stock market. This leads to more and more people flocking towards safer assets like gold. </li><li>Government Taxes & Duties: Government policies go a long way influencing the price of gold on a national and local level. We’re all aware of the duty taxes and gst on gold, and how that influences the retail shoppers and their buying decisions.</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "heading_4t3YHc": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Market Tools For Tracking Prices",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Market Tools For Tracking Prices",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "tools",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_jMrVxj": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>There are a lot of platforms and websites you can use to analyze the gold market live. You can check the MCX gold rate today to get real-time, live data and updates on an hourly basis from the Multi Commodity Exchange. Successful investors use resources like these to stay informed and get the first mover advantage. Checking MCX becomes important as we all know that the gold rates are not just influenced by purity, weight, or general demand and supply but also economical, political, and sentimental events.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
