    "information_content_info_Ak8Q8z": {
      "type": "information-content-info",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_PqakWF": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Gold Price Forecast & Predictions",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Gold Price Forecast & Predictions",
            "heading_level": "h2",
            "heading_id": "forecast",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_WHVNg7": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>While predicting gold prices is not easy as it is influenced by a variety of factors.You can look at the past trends, historic data, and market signals to anticipate a rise or fall in prices. Multiple analysts and financial institutions have released their own gold price predictions for the next 5 years. Majority of these analysts agree that as inflation continues to rise, and economies become volatile, more and more people will make stable investments leading to an increase in gold prices. Gold price prediction 2025 states that gold prices may break all-time highs and will become an excellent investment for medium-term planning. Some financial institutions project a 8 - 12% annual increase, depending on global economy and geopolitical tensions.</p>"
          }
        },
        "heading_7VGy8R": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Gold Price Forecast For India",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_h6NcBt": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Gold price India prediction focuses on increased domestic demand especially during auspicious festivities and wedding seasons. In India, rural buyers continue to contribute and form a major chunk of gold demand, helping gold prices resist the economic dips. It’s best to consider gold price forecasts when planning a gold purchase or a large investment, however they’re not a guarantee of whether gold prices are going to rise or drop. Even as gold prices continue their steady rise over time, you will notice certain weeks where gold prices dropped. It is best to treat these periods as smart investment opportunities to make large investments or your planned gold purchases. </p><p>While gold price predictions and forecasts serve as excellent guides for planning your purchase, you should also stay updated on the latest gold price news from reputable financial platforms such as news channels and online websites for expert opinions and real-time updates.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
