        },
        "heading_W8jRKT": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Digital & Paper-Based Investments",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Digital & Paper-Based Investments",
            "heading_level": "h2",
            "heading_id": "digital",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_deFVdh": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Plenty of investors prefer not to hold physical gold, afraid of thefts and robberies. You can explore some smart and futuristic investment options that include:</p><ul><li>Gold ETFs: Check out the Gold ETF price today and start investing as Gold ETFs offer direct exposure to gold prices via stock exchanges. </li><li>Gold Funds ETF: These are managed funds that track gold assets. </li><li>Gold Mutual Funds: These funds don’t purchase physical gold but invest in companies that are involved in gold mining or similar sectors. </li></ul><p>You can also track the gold share price India and invest in companies that are directly involved in the gold ecosystem. </p>"
          }
        }
      },
