          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>The reason traditional Indian families love gold so much is because as beautiful as it is when worn as jewelry, it can also act as a financial cushion in tough times. Gold loans offer quick disbursals with minimal documentation, making it an increasingly popular choice at times of urgent need.</p>"
          }
        },
        "heading_388PN6": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "How Do Gold Loans Work?",
          "settings": {
            "text": "How Do Gold Loans Work?",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "work",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_E6rkdH": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Banks and NBFCs allow you to deposit your gold as collateral in exchange for instant funds. They look at the gold quantity, purity, and today gold resale value to determine the amount that needs to be sanctioned. Gold loans have become the primary choice for financing personal business ventures, education costs and fees, weddings, and during emergencies as the interest rates for gold loans are usually lower than those of personal and business loans. This is because the gold serves as a secure collateral and reduces the risk from the bank’s end. You also get the flexibility of payment options, allowing you EMIs or one shot payments.<br/><br/></p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_KQ4HtD",
        "richtext_JLBamp",
        "heading_388PN6",
        "richtext_E6rkdH"
      ],
      "name": "Gold As Collateral: Gold Loans & Resale Value",
      "settings": {
        "full_width": false,
        "section_id": "",
