    "faq_section_RcjXbX": {
      "type": "faq-section",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_item_VmY6G9": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "What is the 22 Karat Gold Rate Today in {{ page.metafields.custom.city_name.value }}?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Today, as per India Bullion And Jewellers Association (IBJA), the Gold Rate for 22 Karat Gold is [gold_rate_22kt].</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_cTmyrT": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "What is the price of 24kt Gold in {{ page.metafields.custom.city_name.value }} Today?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Today, the price of 24kt Gold in {{ page.metafields.custom.city_name.value }} as per India Bullion And Jewellers Association (IBJA) is [gold_rate_24kt].</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_4gCdVQ": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "How much is 22Kt Gold Today?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Today, the rate of 22k gold as per India Bullion And Jewellers Association (IBJA) is [gold_rate_22kt].</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_6dUJHg": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "Is 916 Gold 22kt or 24kt?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>916 Gold refers to Gold’s purity every 1000 pieces. Meaning, it is 91.6% pure, which coincides with the purity of 22kt gold.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_hb7WW6": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "What is the 24 karat Gold Rate in {{ page.metafields.custom.state_name.value }} today?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Today, as per the India Bullion And Jewellers Association (IBJA), the Gold Rate for 24 karat gold is [gold_rate_24kt].</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_xF9PGM": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "How much is 1 gram of Gold Today?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>The price of 1 gram of gold depends on its purity, among other factors. Today, as per India Bullion And Jewellers Association (IBJA), the price of 24k gold is [gold_rate_24kt] and the price for 22k gold is [gold_rate_22kt].</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_fwJetY": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "Do Jewellers in {{ page.metafields.custom.city_name.value }} offer different Gold Rates?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Yes, jewellers in {{ page.metafields.custom.city_name.value }} might offer Gold Rates for the same purity even though their base prices for these rates are generally aligned with daily rates published by the India Bullion And Jewellers Association (IBJA). This usually depends on factors like the jeweller’s brand value, physical location, discounts, and more.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_pBeC6M": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "What factors influence the Gold Rate in {{ page.metafields.custom.city_name.value }}?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Gold rates in {{ page.metafields.custom.city_name.value }} are influenced by various factors like IBJA rates, international gold prices, currency exchange rates, import duties and taxes, government policies, stock market, and general demand and supply, to name a few.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_GFzNfQ": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "Why is there price difference between 22kt and 24kt gold in {{ page.metafields.custom.city_name.value }}?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Usually, the base price of 22kt gold is 91.6% of 24kt gold. This is due to the difference in purity, as 24kt gold is 99.9% pure while 22kt gold is only 91.6% pure.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_APW4xA": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "How to check the purity of Gold in {{ page.metafields.custom.city_name.value }}",
            "faq_answer": "<p>In modern times, every gold jewelry bought from a credible and trusted jeweler comes with BIS Hallmarking. You can verify the purity using the HUID online. Alternatively, you can get it checked at a BIS-certified assaying Centre for a minimal cost.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_cpnEpH": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "What are the tax charges on Gold purchase?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>In 2025, you’re liable to pay 3% GST when purchasing gold coins or bars, and an additional 5% GST on making charges when purchasing any form of jewellery. </p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_ARUhAT": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "How many grams of Gold are present in one ‘tola’ gold.",
            "faq_answer": "<p>One ‘Tola’ is an Indian traditional unit of measure still prevalent in the Gold trade. 1 tola refers to 11.66 grams.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_MXDNTn": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "Is 1g equal to 1tola gold?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>No, 1 gram is not equal to 1 tola of gold. Tola is a traditional Indian unit of measurement which equals 11.66 grams of gold.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_yQGXxw": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "How many grams is Tulam gold?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>One Tulam is often used interchangeably in the southern parts of India, like Kerala and Tamil Nadu. One Tulam, or Tola of gold, is equal to 11.66 grams of gold. </p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_yHzi3w": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "How much Tola is 1kg Gold?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Tola is a traditional Indian measurement which roughly equals 11.66 grams. Since 1kg is 1000 grams, we can divide it by 11.66 to find out how many tolas equal 1 kg. The answer? 1 kg is 85.735 tolas.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_DTzy9W": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "Is 14kt Gold good quality?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>14kt gold, or 14 Karat gold, is an excellent choice to make jewelry as it is more resistant to tarnish and scratches when compared to higher purities, making it ideal for daily wear jewelry.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_Etr4Pf": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "Is 14Kt Gold real or fake?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>14Kt Gold is real gold, but it is usually the lowest purity of gold you can purchase in India.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_RmcmKM": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "What is the GST on Gold?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>When making any Gold purchase in India, you’re liable to pay 3% GST (Goods & Services Tax) on the Gold (coins, bars, etc.) and an additional 5% GST on making charges if you’re purchasing gold jewelry.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_fRT8rc": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "What is the custom duty tax on gold?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>As per 2025, you’re paying 6% duty tax on gold (5% customs duty + 1% cess), 3% GST on any purchase of gold, and an additional 5% GST on making charges if you’re purchasing gold jewelry. </p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_Ar38YL": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "Is 916 Hallmark 22kt or 24kt?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>916 hallmark refers to its purity of 91.6% which coincides with 22kt Gold Purity.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_Ug4mnM": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "How is Gold Jewelry Hallmarked?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Gold purity is first tested using XRF or the fire assay method at a BIS-approved Assaying and Hallmarking Centre. Then, the BIS Logo, Purity Mark, 6-digit HUID, and Assaying Centre’s Mark are laser-etched onto the jewelry piece.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_MCNq3p": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "What is the Hallmark stamp for 22kt gold?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>The hallmark stamp for 22kt gold will include the BIS Logo, a 916 Purity Mark (meaning the gold is 91.6% pure), a 6-digit HUID, and the Assaying Centre’s Mark laser etched onto the jewelry piece.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_rQh4TR": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "Is Hallmark compulsory for Gold?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Yes, in India, hallmarking for gold is compulsory except for gold coins and bars. This is to ensure the authenticity of the gold bought from vendors. Buying or selling unmarked gold jewelry can be illegal.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
